# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Method SkColor getColor(int x, int y) const


Converts the pixel at the specified coordinate to an unpremultiplied SkColor. Note: this ignores any SkColorSpace information, and may return lower precision data than is actually in the pixel. Alpha only colortypes (e.g. kAlpha_8_SkColorType) return black with the appropriate alpha set.  The value is undefined for kUnknown_SkColorType or if x or y are out of bounds, or if the pixtap does not have any pixels. / #Param x  ##

#Param y  ##
#Return ##

#Example
